<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-06-23T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-06-23T19:00:00-05:00" n="209" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d209">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/7996: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Peck</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-24T08:00:00+08:00">June 24, 1936—8
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received June 24—7 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>198. 1. Foreign Office has issued a denial of Japanese press reports that
                            Suma gave Chinese Minister of Foreign Affairs on June 19th a “stern
                            warning” against the “continuation of malicious propaganda” against
                            Japan.</p>
                        <p>2. To Department, by mail to Peiping and Tokyo.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Peck</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>